Geographic distribution.
Pseudopaludicola atragula
is a Brazilian endemic species, presently known from two localities in the northwest region of the state of São Paulo, in southeastern Brazil : the type locality (municipality of Icém,
20 º 21 ’ 33 ”S
;
49 º 11 ’ 55 ”W
), and the district of Nova Itapirema, municipality of Nova Aliança (
21 º04’ 54 ”S
;
49 º 31 ’ 11 ”W
), approximately 100 km in a straight line southwards from Icém.
